tip.text: Pretty good spicy miso ramen. Only interesting thing is the servers were speaking in Thai and instead of seaweed I got a piece of green veg...
To get to the new mall Paya Lebar Square, take Exit A. Walk straight to destination. Journey time about 3 minutes.
Must order butter chicken, fish masala, Tandoori malai chicken tikka. Choose your spicy level. And yes I had my lovely dal-makhani with extra spicy. Yums!
Fried rice $6.50 & fried rice special $8.00, diff just for an egg. Choose wisely. Fried rice is good though and curry's pretty alright. Skip the egg curry - it's just hard boiled eggs with curry.
Batavia beans are great! Good for even long black. But if Thumper is all they have, go only for milk based like latte/flat white or cappuccino.
Try their coffee melange. Served with cream foam that kinda blends well with the coffee brew. Coffee is a tad acidic for my liking but the cream foam makes it up for it.
